Definitions

(for example)

Child[ren] of the family

The [“child of the family” is] / [“children of the family” are]:

[child full name] born on [date];

[child full name] born on [date];

[etc].

Family home

The “family home” means [family home address] registered at HM Land Registry with title number [family home title number].

Other properties

“[Other property name]” means [other property address] registered at HM Land Registry with title number [title number];

[etc].

Mortgages

“The [insert] mortgage” means the mortgage secured upon [property name] in favour of [name of mortgagee];

[etc].

Life insurance policies

“The [insert] policy” means the policy or policies issued by [company] and numbered [policy number];

[etc].

“The applicant’s bank accounts” means the following:

the account in the applicant’s sole name with [bank/building society name], with account number [number] and sort code [number];

the account in the applicant’s sole name with [bank/building society name], with account number [number] and sort code [number];

[etc].

“The respondent’s bank accounts” means the following:

the account in the respondent’s sole name with [bank/building society name], with account number [number] and sort code [number];

the account in the respondent’s sole name with [bank/building society name], with account number [number] and sort code [number];

[etc].

“The joint bank accounts” means the following:

the account in the parties’ joint names with [bank/building society name], with account number [number] and sort code [number];

the account in the parties’ joint names with [bank/building society name], with account number [number] and sort code [number];

[etc].

“CMS” means the Child Maintenance Service or such other state appointed agency operating within the United Kingdom as may have preceded it or as may replace it.

“CMS calculation” means the assessment or calculation or periodic demand by the CMS.

Pensions

“[Pension name]” means the pension arrangement/plan held by the [applicant] / [respondent] with [scheme/plan provider name] with reference number [number];
